      "text": "Cowboy Coders are programmers who write code according to their own rules.  They may be very good at writing code, but it doesn't generally follow the standards, processes, policies, or anything else derived from the group.  Cowboy Coders work well alone, or in the old-style [[Cave Programmer]] environment, but they rarely, if ever, work well in a team.  Often times, they are a burr in the saddle that keeps the team from getting positive work done.",
